body.description: The PNY Elite-X Fit USB 3.1 Flash Drive is built for speed and convenience, making it the ideal solution for large files and demanding applications. With read speeds of up to 200MB/s, the Elite-X Fit USB 3.1 Flash Drive is up to 30x faster than standard PNY USB 2.0 Flash Drives. PNY's Elite-X Fit USB 3.1 Flash Drive is designed with convenience and portability in mind. Not only does it allow for the fast transfer and storage of files, the Elite-X Fit's micro-sized, low profile design is perfect for long-stay applications; it can be left in a desktop or laptop's USB port for an extended period of time, without interfering with everyday usage. It is compatible with USB 3.1 Gen 1/USB 3.0 equipped PC and Mac desktop and laptop computers, in-car stereos, game consoles, printers, and TV’s, and backwards compatible with USB 2.0.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars PNY 64GB Elite-X A Compact Power Flash USB drive for Quick Data Transfer
reviews.reviewText: the PNY 64GB Elite-X Fit USB 3.1 Flash Drive, and I must say, it has exceeded my expectations in every way. This little device is a true gem, and here's why I'm so impressed:Blazing Fast Speeds:The standout feature of this flash drive is its remarkable speed. With a transfer rate of up to 200MB/s, it's lightning-fast. Whether I'm copying large files, backing up important documents, or transferring high-definition videos, the Elite-X Fit gets the job done in a fraction of the time compared to other drives I've used.Compact and Durable Design:This flash drive is incredibly compact, making it ideal for on-the-go professionals like me. Its low-profile design allows it to sit flush with the USB port, preventing it from sticking out and potentially getting damaged. The build quality feels sturdy, and the metal casing adds a sense of durability, giving me confidence that my data is safe.Generous Storage Capacity:64GB is a sweet spot for a flash drive. It offers ample storage for a wide range of files, from documents and photos to music and videos. It's perfect for those who need a reliable and spacious portable storage solution without carrying around a bulky external hard drive.Plug-and-Play Simplicity:Using the Elite-X Fit is a breeze. It's a true plug-and-play device that works seamlessly with Windows, macOS, and even some smart TVs and gaming consoles. No need to install drivers or go through complicated setup processes – just plug it in and start transferring files.Value for Money:In terms of price-to-performance ratio, the PNY Elite-X Fit is an excellent value. You're getting top-tier transfer speeds and build quality at a very reasonable price point, making it a smart investment for anyone seeking fast and reliable data storage.In summary, the PNY 64GB Elite-X Fit USB 3.1 Flash Drive is a fantastic piece of technology. Its exceptional speed, compact design, generous storage capacity, and plug-and-play convenience make it an outstanding choice for everyday users and professionals alike. I highly recommend this flash drive to anyone in need of a portable storage solution that combines speed, reliability, and affordability. It's a winner in my book!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Pretty good but not as good
reviews.reviewText: Picked this flash drive up with the intended use as a LiveCD for a Raspberry Pi setup.Reading some reviews online it received mixed reviews on this intended usage. Some stated it was a good value while others gave the impression it was pretty good. For basic transfer of files it was speedy and worked fine. Once I flashed the OS onto the drive and installed it into the Raspberry Pi and booted up the mediocre performance came front and center. It took about 30 minutes for the OS to get booted in and to run updates on the system. While this is not bad it is far from a quality experience. The read/write performance falls down unfortunately. Boot time on the system and miscellaneous files is just average.If you are using this device for basic files copy / paste it will work fine for what it does. BUT If you are looking for something for LiveCD / Raspberry Pi usage it will not perform well for the task.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It works great just as advertised for my Blink Camera System
reviews.reviewText: I bought 256GB Version of the Sandisk for my Blink Camera System. After 60 GB of Video Files The Files showed up as invalid. I tested both on my computer with both NTFS & eFat file system. Both disk & file systems reacted the same. I called San Disk because the Amazon Return said to send it in original packing. They tried to blame it on the Blink system but finally agreed to let me mail it to them so they could test it & sent me replacements if I wasn't stupid. I then Called Amazon very upset. They agreed to let me return it. I bought the PNY version of the 256 GB usb drive, It worked Great. Buy the PNY instead.
